						<summary>

						<p>On a broken slab set up in the compound of the Hanumān temple.</p>						

						<p>1014-15 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 936, Ānanda, corresponding to 1014-15 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It records a deed of settlement <hi rend="italic">(saṁsthā-patra)</hi> made in favour of the <hi rend="italic">Ūroḍeyas</hi> and the <hi rend="italic">Gāvuṇḍas</hi> of Kandagale by the chief Gōyindapayyarasa.</p>						

